##
## life cycle
##

git add . :: Add a directory
git status -s :: Check what all are part of commit
git commit -m 'comment' :: commit on local repo
git push origin master :: To commit changes on the server repo
   git push [remote] [branch] 
##

git branch [name] :: Create new branch
git switch [name] :: Switch branch
git push origin [name_of_your_new_branch] :: Push same branch on the remote server
git remote add [name_of_your_remote] [name_of_your_new_branch] :: Create a remote

##

# Create a ssh key for git

1. Create ssh key
   ->ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "saifnaqviit3019@gmail.com"
   -> ed25519: is the algo
2. Start agent in backgroud: eval
   -> eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
3. add key to ssh-agent
   -> ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
4. goto github.com/Snaqvi-PROJ -> Profile -> Settings -> SSH and GPG keys -> New ssh key -> Add ssh key -> confirm passwordwq

# Create personal access token:
1. Github -> Settings -> Developer Settings -> personal access tokens
2. Select Expiration, Select repo
3. Generate token
4. Copy the token to wherever is required.
